<br>
Aggro Management.<br>
<br>
I am not really interested on how to hold aggro while tanking Mob XYZ, rather more general info.<br>
<br>
If I understand it correctly most mob  hatred level will depend on: <br>
<br>
1. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Direct Damage Done</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Weapon damage, proc damage, Martial damage)<br>
<br>
2. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Not Damaging procs</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> like Tashani, Snare, Slow, Blind etc<br>
<br>
3. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Proximity</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (it will aggro more on whoevere closer,  if all do similar damage)<br>
<br>
4. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Faction.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
5. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Game tricks</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> like siting in front of the mob, beging etc.<br>
<br>
<br>
So when would MOB hate me more:<br>
(Assume STR STA DEX are maxed with Enchanter/Shaman buffs and all weapons skills areat the same level)<br>
<br>
<br>
a.  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_item_info.html?num=19715" target="top">Stone Bladed Edge </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Primary and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_item_info.html?num=30071" target="top">Club of the Ice Ocean </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Seconadary<br>
which proc 135 and 149 DD respectively and both relativly fast.<br>
<br>
b. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_item_info.html?num=6618" target="top">Journeyman's Walking Stick</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Primary and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_item_info.html?num=5643" target="top">Silken Whip of Ensnaring</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Secondary<br>
<br>
So &quot;a&quot; or &quot;b&quot; will make my aggro holdeing job easier ?<br>
<br>
Or would it be just as effective as swinging <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_item_info.html?num=25979" target="top">Windblade</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> ?<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=102838&amp;resize=true" target="top">Tiny <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Tinyone</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=251494&amp;resize=true" target="top">Tall <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Enchy</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=359284&amp;resize=true" target="top">Mighty <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Bucha</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=102843&amp;resize=true" target="top">Stealthy <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Zokro</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=warriorbucha>WarriorBucha</A> at: 2/14/03 2:07:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=planetium>Planetium</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.covad.net/~swing4daddy/eyes_066.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/03 2:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2912.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> Actually, procs are really the most reliable way to build agro in the current broken state of the game. Your best bet is Stone Bladed Edge Primary and J-Stick secondary, going purely for agro that is.<br>
<br>
<br>
I assume they both proc at an average rate. SOme weapons do have a tendency to proc more... like Kunzar Ku'Juch never procs while Bloodfrenzy procs a lot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/03 12:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2912.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about holding aggro</span><hr size=1> Your aggro has very little to do with the damage you actually deal.  All the mob cares about is how damaging the weapon you're swinging at him *could* be.  Today a friend was using the 36/20 monk 2HB and it pulled considerably more aggro than his 17/20 17/19 DW combination despite the latter combination actually doing more damage (or so he says).  Mobs really only care about ratios when dealing with attacking-related aggro.<br>
<br>
All procs have some preset aggro.  It's not that damage isn't good aggro but things such as stun, slow, or snare produce incredibly high amount of aggro.  If we can proc Strike of Solusek Ro you bet that will be a reliable aggro proc but the best thing we get, not counting Anarchy on SoD, is around 150 (Wrath of Fire/Ice/Wind series) which is relatively tame for aggro purposes.  Just imagine you're a wizard casting 150 DDs at random intervals.  The mob could care less about your 150 DD nukes when your casters are nuking it with 2K nukes. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyrdlan>Wyrdlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/18/03 2:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2912.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eq-viatores.org/book.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about holding aggro</span><hr size=1> Not to mention on Anarchy it's the STUN that gets you, not the damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lewterpitt>LEWTERPITT</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.socal.rr.com/moshpitt/shadowdevils/images/pics/inmybelly-.gif width=50 height=30" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/03 3:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2912.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about holding aggro</span><hr size=1> Windblade is the way to go <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Unless you're in a pop zone where mobs hit for insane amounts of damage you'll do fine, its not going to be your fault if the sk or necro dots for all they're worth in the first 10sec, or the wizard offloads his most powerful spell in the first 10sec before sitting down for the next mob or the dru/rng snares when inc.<br>
<br>
Anyways, dont hurt yourself by using those crap ass 1 dmg : 3dly or so weapons. Mosters still hate the person doing the most damage to them, and hitting for 30 per hit isnt gonna be pretty especially if the sk or paladin does 100-200 per pop.<br>
<br>
So, stick to windblade.  <p>Lewter - Rodcet <br>
www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234885<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xenojones>XENOJONES</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 586<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/03 2:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2912.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about holding aggro</span><hr size=1> Windblade can't be all that great. I don't have one, but did use a Shovel of the harvest for a while which has the same damage, but 1 delay faster than windblade.I could hold aggro with it, but had to work extra hard and it still paled in comparison to two 1handers. 2H weapons can hold aggro, but have a tough time grabbing it. I have found that faster weapons will get me aggro early faster then I can switch to a 2hander if needed or a good 1Hander + shield if I am worried about riposts. When we were trying 4th warder we had a bitch of a time figuring out how to keep aggro on the tank and off the clerics. When I used a 16 delay in primary and 15 delay in secondary I was able to hold aggro well, where dual SODs were not able to. Procs are a great way to hold aggro, but there is no guarantee they will proc. I have used a BF/HG combo and have gone 2 or 3 minutes without a proc a few times.<br>
<br>
<br>
